Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.22,0:07:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The brutality is spreading like a contagion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the Psycho-Hazard grown by this much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.47,0:07:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, it's become a full-blown riot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.43,0:07:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The Area Stress Level is rising like crazy too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:19.36,skroll,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\an8\move(1800,25,-180,25)\blur0.6\c&H93E789&}Aren't they just latent criminals from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.02,0:07:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just the helmet-wearers who've gone on a rampage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.96,0:07:20.78,skroll,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\move(1800,555,-280,555)\blur0.6\c&H89A9EA&}Must be a Psycho-Hazard...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:22.57,skroll,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\an8\move(1800,25,-180,25)\blur0.6\c&H89D5DE&}It's begun...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.09,0:07:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Scared citizens are committing widespread acts of violence all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.44,0:07:24.41,skroll,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\move(1800,265,-280,265)\blur0.6\c&HC1C377&}Someone without a helmet on is going on a rampage?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.36,0:07:26.42,skroll,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)\an8\move(1800,25,-180,25)\blur0.6\c&HBBCF63&\t(\blur5.5)}Run! Run! Run! Run! Run! Ruuuuuuun!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief Kasei issued an emergency summons.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,She's ordering all CID personnel to report for duty, including those who are off duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.67,0:07:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You sound restless.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.50,0:07:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, of course. This situation would make anyone uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.68,0:07:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's awaiting us from here on out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.96,0:07:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to this town?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I really like that ordinary side of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.20,0:07:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are both quite ordinary, essentially common people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.39,0:08:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never thought of myself as avaricious.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.41,0:08:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I just long for a world in which everyday things are done in an everyday way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.43,0:08:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I really want.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we are, two ordinary, unremarkable people...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.16,0:08:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,instigating crime in a town that isn't ordinary at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.55,0:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A town that isn't ordinary, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.14,0:08:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This town is like a parody of one of the old novels I used to read.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.85,0:08:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the ones by William Gibson?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.09,0:08:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,More like Philip K. Dick, perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.38,0:08:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not as controlling as the society George Orwell depicted, and it's not as wild as what Gibson depicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.54,0:08:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I've never read Dick.{bullshit you are the secondmost gay character in this show}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.04,0:08:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Which book would you recommend I read first?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.48,0:08:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,"Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.97,0:08:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They based an old movie on that story, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.45,0:08:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, though the original is quite different.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You should compare them when you have time someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.68,0:08:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go ahead and download it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.76,0:08:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you buy paper books?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.83,0:09:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,E-books lack character.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.07,0:09:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.76,0:09:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Books aren't just something you read.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.01,0:09:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're like a form of meditation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.71,0:09:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Meditation?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes, when I'm not feeling well, I read books but I don't really absorb them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When that happens, it makes me think about what could be getting in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There are also books that I can absorb even when I'm feeling down.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.99,0:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.87,0:09:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be like mental conditioning.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.67,0:09:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's all about the stimulation your brain receives when you turn the pages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The feeling of flipping them over, one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.21,0:09:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's kind of a downer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.16,0:09:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When I talk with you, I feel like I've been missing out on something all my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.31,0:09:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You're reading too much into it.{get it}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.78,0:09:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.35,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.48,0:10:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.75,0:10:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is just a random thought, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.20,0:10:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.31,0:10:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just too perfect that such an outstanding hacker would be into Gibson.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.49,0:10:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We're currently facing an unprecedented crisis all across the metropolitan area.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.02,0:10:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Sibyl System was introduced, people believed it would eliminate all possibility of a riot among the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the current Public Safety Bureau has neither the personnel nor the equipment to suppress such a mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.35,0:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been at peace for too long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.40,0:10:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We're currently trying to bring in the border security Drones and equip them with non-lethal weapons,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.99,0:10:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but the situation out there requires prompt action.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.27,0:10:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Until a full-fledged suppression unit is formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.70,0:10:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we have no choice but to have those of you at the CID act as the last remaining shield to keep our citizens safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.75,0:10:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The cymatic scan-proof helmets we have observed hinder the functionality of the Dominators.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.53,0:11:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Stun batons are therefore our most effective weapon for dealing with the rioters.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll also permit the use of electromagnetic pulse grenades for crowd control in emergencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.97,0:11:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the helmet's electronics are knocked out by the EMP, you'll be able to use your Dominators in the usual way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.85,0:11:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, make sure you pay careful attention to when you use the grenades.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.20,0:11:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you let off an EMP in the wrong location, you might disable vital city facilities as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.13,0:11:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How many grenades do we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.73,0:11:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Not many.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.29,0:11:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably enough to give out two to each person here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.98,0:11:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll form teams of three.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Each team is to take an area and\N suppress the riots there one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be time-consuming and dangerous, but we don't have any other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole town's future is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on all of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.81,0:12:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I always knew you and I would be traveling down a dangerous road together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.43,0:12:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you never wanted to turn back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.31,0:12:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't you think it's strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.04,0:12:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Sibyl System.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.06,0:12:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All those people who are happy entrusting everything in their lives to some nonsense like that? They're the ones who are crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.19,0:12:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a foreigner, you know. I appreciate simply being able to live in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.38,0:12:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's what I'd like to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.86,0:12:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the end it's just like you said, Makishima.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.55,0:12:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I also desire a world where we can just do everyday things in an everyday way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my hometown. It's where I was born and raised.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.32,0:12:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to put things right as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.69,0:12:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys want to see what lies beyond the destruction you'll cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.04,0:12:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the destruction, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.68,0:12:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that happens, more the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't mind if this is the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.21,0:12:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you going with manipulating information on the 'net?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.20,0:12:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The AI I set up beforehand is already at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.42,0:13:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Makishima Shougo... He's really done it this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.36,0:13:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a sec, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.19,0:13:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We still haven't found conclusive evidence that Makishima has anything to do with these helmet incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.08,0:13:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The moment an ordinary person even thinks of making something that'd undermine the Sibyl System, it shows in their Hue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.39,0:13:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But whoever was behind the helmet designed it,\N mass produced it, and distributed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.75,0:13:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole process probably took a few months at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.45,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd have to order parts, arrange distribution and so on.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.69,0:13:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way he'd be able to do that while avoiding all the scanners around town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.79,0:13:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The only person who could make that helmet
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.94,0:13:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is someone who could defeat the Sibyl System without needing one himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.94,0:13:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So he took advantage of a blind spot in the Sibyl System to engineer a mass Psycho-Hazard?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Makishima's goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.17,0:13:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.10,0:13:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.28,0:13:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Makishima's crimes always had a purpose behind them. He was always looking for answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:14:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a truly fearsome riot, but I can't believe that this chaos could be his only goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.51,0:14:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I agree with you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.50,0:14:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,If all he wanted to do was watch the city burn{shoutouts to brainchild},\N he'd be a lot easier for us to apprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.50,0:14:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch. Things are looking bad online too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.60,0:14:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a mishmash of false rumors and real information flying back and forth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.65,0:14:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we were keeping a lid on media coverage?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.68,0:14:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Made-up rumors attract more attention anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.09,0:14:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.13,0:14:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Bureau's killing all the townspeople"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.39,0:14:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.06,0:14:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you just run them over with the car?{good idea}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.08,0:14:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.28,0:14:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought it was a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.53,0:14:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.07,0:14:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Public Safety Bureau!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.71,0:15:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop this violence immediately and lay down with your hands behind your head!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.96,0:15:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no choice but to resort to force.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.68,0:15:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Give them another warning!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.05,0:15:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Public Safety Bureau!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.91,0:15:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Cease this violence immediately or we'll be forced to use Dominators!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.24,0:15:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We will not hesitate to use lethal force on those of you with high Crime Coefficients!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.23,0:15:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I repeat! Lay down with your hands behind your head!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.32,0:15:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you doing this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.54,0:15:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The guys in helmets are the real criminals!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.90,0:15:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the Bureau going to do about all the helmets that are already out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.33,0:15:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're the victims, aren't we?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.15,0:15:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! You're breaking the law too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.88,0:16:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.32,0:16:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,These guys are victims as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.22,0:16:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.76,0:16:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If the citizens hadn't been dragged into this, they wouldn't have become so violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.43,0:16:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I mean the helmet-wearers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.21,0:16:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It might take time, but eventually they'll all be hunted down and killed, just like this lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.11,0:16:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ones we don't catch will be killed by gangs of citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.12,0:16:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's been bothering me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.20,0:16:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The false rumors on the 'net are getting worse and worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.38,0:16:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What if this is another case of Makishima\N manipulating information for his own purposes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We already know that either he or one of his accomplices is an accomplished hacker.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.43,0:16:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, all those crimes wouldn't have been possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at all those people who\N surrendered and took off their helmets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.54,0:16:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They're scum who'd never be able to commit crimes otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.70,0:17:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In a sense, they're all just Makishima's pawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.05,0:17:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.19,0:17:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, then what {\i1}is{\i0} Makishima's goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.04,0:17:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's suppose that everything is going according to his plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.47,0:17:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he even anticipated what we'd do at this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.25,0:17:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, which riot locations were we asked to suppress first?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.59,0:17:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he's been playing us from the start.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.06,0:17:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What if the whole thing was set up so that the riots would flare up
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.78,0:17:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in such a way that all the CID's detectives would be lured out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.56,0:17:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't mean... No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.59,0:17:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I've spent these last five years desperately trying to figure out the Sibyl System.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.76,0:17:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,"Distributed parallel processing by servers installed throughout the metropolitan area."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,"A model system that makes iron-clad fault tolerance a reality."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.70,0:18:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are the catchphrases used by the Ministry of Welfare.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.48,0:18:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, analyzing and measuring the\N Psycho-Pass of every citizen in this country
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.79,0:18:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,requires a great deal of computing power.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.37,0:18:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,As you might imagine, such computational feats are impossible without distributed computing over a series of nodes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.00,0:18:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the more I looked into it, the more I realized
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.09,0:18:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that something about the flow of data made no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.40,0:18:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Scanners throughout town, authorized \Ncounseling AIs, the Dominators, and so on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.96,0:18:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it looked like the data was just being distributed throughout the grid,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.70,0:18:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was actually just being passed from one place to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:45.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I finally noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.75,0:18:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a single relay point that every piece of data transmitted through the Sibyl System
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.65,0:18:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,passes through at least once, without exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.06,0:18:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If we consider the possibility that there is a stand-alone system hidden there
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.94,0:19:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that is responsible for all of Sibyl's processing and computation,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.95,0:19:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,everything makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.95,0:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.53,0:19:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What's strange, though, is its capacity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.70,0:19:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If everything really is handled by this one system,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.45,0:19:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the sheer throughput it must have is beyond what should be possible with current technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As well as that, it makes no sense to put it all in one place to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.97,0:19:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far too great of a security risk no matter how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.86,0:19:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they just want to keep it secret at all costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.57,0:19:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.80,0:19:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I discover something that fishy, I can't help but sniff around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.98,0:19:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to find out the truth behind the Sibyl System.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.93,0:19:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And you tracked it back to this facility?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the relay point at which all the cymatic scan data intersects.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.82,0:20:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,There are also clear signs that the true power consumption in this area has been concealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.35,0:20:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm almost certain that the Sibyl System resides within this building: the Ministry of Welfare's Nona Tower.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.57,0:20:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.98,0:20:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't we all uncover the heart of the Great Prophetess?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.65,0:20:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Ginoza!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.28,0:20:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The man behind these incidents is planning to attack the Ministry of Welfare's Nona Tower!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The riots are just a diversion!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not to leave your post based on groundless speculation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.67,0:20:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People's lives are at stake!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.03,0:20:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But since all the Inspectors and Enforcers are out on the field, the government district in the Chuo Ward is empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.85,0:20:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The guard Drones might as well be scarecrows to these guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stay here and let them carry out their plan, we won't get a second chance to stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.85,0:21:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let us go, if only us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.44,0:21:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.82,0:21:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys go there first and find out what's happening!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll continue to suppress the riots in each area.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.91,0:21:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything happens, let me know immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.77,0:21:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.80,0:21:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is!
